{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, uncommon questions in ChartQA, such as accurately determining a range of data values, may lead MLLMs to struggle to identify the correct range.",
    "These insights highlight a crucial issue with ChartQA: while it includes a wide range of real-world images and QAs, biases in chart and QA distributions constrain its generalizability.",
    "This emphasizes the need for a dataset incorporating a broader variety of chart types and QAs.",
    "Such a dataset can potentially enhance MLLM's ability to tackle the complex challenges inherent in real-world scenarios.",
    "Instruction Tuning AblationsTo address RQ2, we design a series of ablation studies to examine the effect of different question types and chart-related tasks on CQA, aiming to identify effective visual instructions."
  ]
}